                            <comment id="96782" author="yong.fan" created="Tue, 21 Oct 2014 02:12:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It is another instance of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5301&quot; title=&quot;Test failure sanity-lfsck test_17: (3) unexpected status&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5301&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5301&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="96779" author="yong.fan" created="Tue, 21 Oct 2014 01:42:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There are too much objects left from former other sanity-xxx tests, as to the LFSCK could NOT finish the scanning in the given time. So it is not an interoperability issue, but related with the test environment and test scripts. We have another ticket to adjust the sanity-lfsck test timeout in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5301&quot; title=&quot;Test failure sanity-lfsck test_17: (3) unexpected status&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5301&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5301&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. If we do not want to land patches to b2_6, then we can mark this one as the duplication of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5301&quot; title=&quot;Test failure sanity-lfsck test_17: (3) unexpected status&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5301&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5301&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="96622" author="jlevi" created="Fri, 17 Oct 2014 18:38:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fan Yong,&lt;br/&gt;
Can you comment if this is just a test interop issue?  We aren&apos;t landing patches on b2_6, so we may just ignore this interop test failure.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
